<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->
<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Best Practices</h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:list {"ordered":true} -->
<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Modular Code</strong>: Writing clean, modular code that is easy to maintain and scale.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Documentation</strong>: Keeping thorough documentation for APIs, codebases, and development processes.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Testing</strong>: Implementing unit tests, integration tests, and end-to-end tests to ensure code reliability.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Code_review" data-type="link" data-id="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Code_review">Code Reviews</a></strong>: Regularly reviewing code with peers to catch bugs and improve code quality.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Scalability</strong>: Designing systems that can handle increased load and user growth efficiently.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>
<!-- /wp:list -->

